    • Method Detail

      • determineEndpoint

        public static int determineEndpoint(String remote)
        Determines the type of endpoint
        Parameters:
        remote - String representation of the endpoint
        Returns:
        RemoteAPI.REMOTE_POST if the endpoint is http or https

        RemoteAPI.REMOTE_GCM if the endpoint is an Android GCM key

        RemoteAPI.REMOTE_UNKNOWN if anything else

      • getGCMKey

        public static String getGCMKey()
        Get the Server Application Google Cloud Messaging Key. There is a diffferent one for each server.
        Returns:
        App Server GCM key

      • getGCMDry

        public static boolean getGCMDry()
        Get if DRY mode: messages to GCM are handled OK, but not actually delivered to clients. For testing purposes.
        Returns:
        true if in DRY mode (no messages sent to clients)

      • getGCMCrypt

        public static String getGCMCrypt()
        Get encryption key for messages sent through GCM.
        Returns:
        The path to the key to use for encryption, or null if encryption is disabled

      • getLogDebug

        public static boolean getLogDebug()
        Determine if additional debug logging is available. This is used when the information to be logged may contain sensitive data.
        Returns:
        true if everything should be logged

      • getDBPath

        public static String getDBPath(ModuleContext context)
        Get the path where the folder containing the DB will be read/created. Only used if using Derby DB persistence (default).
        Returns:
        Path to folder of the DB

      • getRemovalTime

        public static Long getRemovalTime()
        Get the value, in milliseconds, of time at which removal of older stored data will be removed. Only for Derby DB Persistence.
        Returns:
        Minimum age, in milliseconds, at which the data will be removed (data older than this will be removed)

      • getContext

        public static String getContext()
        Get the context path part of the URL to be used as "alias" when registering the servlet.
        Returns:
        Context Path of URL

      • getHardcoded

        public static boolean getHardcoded()
        Determine if hardcoded registration of the servlet, with basic authentication, has been set. If not, the servelt will have to be registered by the web container using its own configuration methods (might require packaging this project as a .war), and also the authenticatino measures.
        Returns:
        true if hardcoded registration of the servlet is enabled

      • getGETenabled

        public static boolean getGETenabled()
        Get if GET debug mode is enabled. If so, GET HTTP Request will be accepted just like if they were POST.
        Returns:
        true if GET requests are accepted.
